<item>
            <title>[SPARK-16941] SparkSQLOperationManager should use synchronized Map to store SessionHandle</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-16941</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I had run a high concurrency sql query with thriefserver, I found this error without any previous error:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Error: java.util.NoSuchElementException: key not found: SessionHandle &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;a2ea264f-d29d-43c4-842f-4e0f2a3cf877&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; (state=,code=0)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I check the code in &lt;b&gt;SparkSQLOperationManager&lt;/b&gt;, and found the &lt;b&gt;Map(sessionToContexts and sessionToActivePool)&lt;/b&gt; is not thread safe in it.&lt;br/&gt;
I found this error in version 1.5.1 but I think the last master branch will still have this error.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
